    </button>

    <div id="insights-content" class="doha-insights-collapsible">
      <div class="doha-insight-grid reveal">
        <div class="doha-insight">
          <span class="doha-insight-number">01</span>
          <h3>AI as Infrastructure, Not Just Tool</h3>
          <p>Participants recognized that AI isn't merely another software tool—it's foundational infrastructure that will reshape how every sector operates, similar to electricity or the internet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doha-insight">
          <span class="doha-insight-number">02</span>
          <h3>The Readiness Gap is Institutional</h3>
          <p>The challenge isn't technological capability—it's institutional readiness. Organizations, policies, and mental models haven't kept pace with AI's advancement.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doha-insight">
          <span class="doha-insight-number">03</span>
          <h3>Cross-Sector Dialogue is Essential</h3>
          <p>No single sector has the complete picture. Healthcare sees patient implications, education sees workforce shifts, government sees policy gaps—each perspective is partial but necessary.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doha-insight">
          <span class="doha-insight-number">04</span>
          <h3>Urgency Without Panic</h3>
          <p>The conversation revealed a shared sense that action is needed now, but thoughtful action—not reactive fear. Preparation, not prediction, emerged as the guiding principle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

